  "prompt": "International awards of Shahrukh Khan?",
  "response": "Shah Rukh Khan, often referred to as the \"King of Bollywood,\" has received numerous international awards and recognitions throughout his career. Here are some notable international awards:\n\n1. **Crystal Award** - Presented by the World Economic Forum in 2018 for his leadership in advocating for children's rights and promoting social causes.\n\n2. **Ordre des Arts et des Lettres** - Awarded by the French government in 2014, this honor recognizes significant contributions to the arts, including film.\n\n3. **Asian Film Awards** - He has received multiple nominations and won awards at this prestigious ceremony.\n\n4. **International Indian Film Academy (IIFA) Awards** - Although these are primarily awarded in India, the IIFAs often take place in various international locations, highlighting Indian cinema globally.\n\n5. **Best Asian Actor** - Received at the 2005 European Film Awards.\n\n6. **Star of the Year Award** - Presented at the 2014 Dubai International Film Festival.\n\n7. **Global Diversity Award** - Recognized at the 2013 *Global Diversity Forum* for his influence in promoting Indian cinema worldwide.\n\n8. **Ambassador for UNESCO's \"Let's Read\" initiative** - Recognized for promoting reading and literacy in underprivileged communities.\n\nIn addition to these awards, Shah Rukh Khan is widely celebrated for his films and has a massive fan following globally, making him one of the most recognized faces in cinema. His influence extends beyond film into social and humanitarian efforts, earning him various honors around the world.",
